@startuml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
actor User
participant "SolidJS UI" as SolidJS
participant "Stockfish Web Worker\n(hints / hover)" as StockfishWorker
participant "Bun Server\n(apps/server)" as Server
participant "Orchestrator\n(in-process)" as Orch
participant "EngineBridge\n(→ native Stockfish / lc0)" as Engine
participant "OllamaLlmClient" as Llm

== Hint Request Flow (Local Worker) ==
User -> SolidJS: Clicks "Get Hint"
SolidJS -> StockfishWorker: uci / isready (once)
SolidJS -> StockfishWorker: position fen <current>
SolidJS -> StockfishWorker: go depth 10
StockfishWorker --> SolidJS: bestmove e2e4
SolidJS -> User: Displays hint (bestmove)

== Hover Blunder Flow (Local Worker) ==
User -> SolidJS: Hovers candidate move square
SolidJS -> StockfishWorker: position fen <after hypothetical move>
SolidJS -> StockfishWorker: go depth 6
StockfishWorker --> SolidJS: info score cp -250 ...
SolidJS -> User: Hover override advice + shocked emotion

== Replayability Flow (Local History) ==
User -> SolidJS: Clicks "Back" / "Forward"
SolidJS -> SolidJS: Update currentIndex in gameState
SolidJS -> User: Renders historical FEN (no API call)

== Standard Move Flow (Move + Advice) ==
User -> SolidJS: Click-to-move (e2 -> e4)
SolidJS -> Server: POST /move { humanMoveSan: "e4",\nfenAfterHuman: "<fen>", difficulty: "<difficulty>" }
Server -> Orch: executeTurn(humanMoveSan, difficulty)  ' in-process

note over Orch, Engine: AI move generation (Maia + Stockfish FEN derivation)

Orch -> Engine: getEvaluation / getMaiaMove / getFenAfterMove
Engine --> Orch: AI move (Maia) + resulting FEN (Stockfish)

Orch --> Server: { fen: "<updated>", move: "e7e5" }
Server --> SolidJS: HTTP 200 OK { fen: "<updated>", move: "e7e5" }
SolidJS -> User: Renders updated position

SolidJS -> Server: POST /advice { humanMove: "e4", aiMove: "e7e5", fen: "<updated>" }

note over Orch, Llm: Coaching commentary generation

Server -> Orch: generateAdviceStream(...)
Orch -> Engine: getEvaluation (context)
Engine --> Orch: score cp 45
Orch -> Llm: promptStream(SYSTEM_PROMPT, structured prompt)  ' prompt via engine-core
Llm --> Orch: commentary tokens (buffered → extractCommentary)
Orch --> Server: single cleaned commentary chunk
Server --> SolidJS: HTTP 200 text/plain stream
SolidJS -> User: Displays coach advice (and emotion)

@enduml
